<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4353] Create VersionedWritable interface that allows a class version and an instance version</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4353</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Here is comment from Lars (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-2195&quot; title=&quot;Support cyclic replication&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-2195&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-2195&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;):&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When we did versioning for a project I used to work on a long time ago, we had maintained a class version &lt;b&gt;and&lt;/b&gt; an instance version. We might need both.&lt;br/&gt;
The class should know which version it is, but also it is useful in many scenarios to ask the instance what specific version it is on.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I.e. we need an interface with two methods: One to get the class version, one to get the instance version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This would apply to HLogKey which is able to read entries without explicit version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
